<subSubSection id="1BC896BDF44CA8647580D7B1E2A17EC1" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="description">
<paragraph id="168F58B03BDA2F433F5BF0FFD34B4C7F" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Measurements.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D3E1BFB0A7E055317A7966B1567DA286" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
Total length: male 3.0-3.5 mm (
<emphasis id="51509C8A05492D0F3F95D9B6B6A8D080" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">N</emphasis>
= 4), female 5.1 mm (
<emphasis id="E41AA3CD8E54598A10C01F28E3F22D36" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">N</emphasis>
= 1).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4AAA1C9A59AB1DEFF9795D10E9FB1AC3" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="7D6BA6389B31D8B9E3EEFA9460D49FA7" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E1EA1F98F7AB2F492920EA00F29C660" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
The salient features of the new species include: general color (Figs 
<figureCitation id="66FE441C571FE6A4939C8160E3F8C06F" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="85632BB1BB643DD4F22A8634266DBCF8" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">6</figureCitation>
) yellowish white; dorsolateral and middle parts of anal tube (Figs 
<figureCitation id="5DC8A6ABD1D553075F0D6CEA3AA87E6D" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="D14874ABB8E3AB1C09750A61A28EFDD9" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38</figureCitation>
) each with a finger-like process; outer process of gonostyli (Figs 
<figureCitation id="BF01F02D3392F7E8661021E6F1E4D5D2" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="25FD0324BED2B21BB15549F14560C220" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38</figureCitation>
) convex and arcuate with nearly square process at apex in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FE7A3127D711C0310FF8C00F6C653C96" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="coloration">
<paragraph id="9BC14EC2890C0F7CCED0811F5D8F22C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Coloration.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A9DF3294150DDB8E69B9C430BE615B62" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
General color yellowish white (Figs 
<figureCitation id="24F2CA386007DF98AF1BA7A83E9DA5A6" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="F9DB82362A3ED4738C33797C481A17F3" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">6</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum light brown. Eyes black. Legs yellowish brown. Tegmina semitransparent. Wings hyaline. Abdomen yellowish white.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5A84DD7887796D79CC5284AC0C38567F" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="head and thorax">
<paragraph id="321C6DF3E0E07D5A5B94B73D482935E8" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Head and thorax.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8FD91D87DD030B936BD5C56D31C550D4" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
Head (Figs 
<figureCitation id="5142DB4FE6BDEA3930E7A7DADE92130F" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Metanigrus chromus sp. nov., male 1 dorsal view 2 lateral view. Metanigrus guttatus sp. nov., male 3 dorsal view 4 lateral view. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 5 dorsal view 6 lateral view. Metanigrus spinatus sp. nov., male 7 dorsal view 8 lateral view. Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520803" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="CEFD4ED6AFD8CB32C74373D81F38DFD4" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">31</figureCitation>
) significantly narrower than pronotum, without median carina. Vertex shorter in middle line than wide at base (1: 1.99), with two posterolateral areolets at base not meeting medially. Frons (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D1AA27F3F8B9EB243EC3962B3998441D" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">32</figureCitation>
) subrectangular, without median carina, longer in middle line than wide at widest portion (about 1.93: 1), lateral carinae with a dense row of sensory pits along outer margin. Postclypeus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9E49FF3A1A6F2797B11B69E524299931" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">32</figureCitation>
) with distinct median and lateral carinae. Frontoclypeal suture nearly straight. Rostrum elongate, surpassing hind-coxae. Pronotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7C25804C4CE7BD29C21FFE22E55D16DC" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">31</figureCitation>
) wider than maximum width of head (including eyes) (1.43: 1), with median carina and sinuate lateral carinae. Mesonotum (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B065C4706735F9CDE6079ECF823417E6" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">31</figureCitation>
) about 5.96 times longer than pronotum in midline, with distinct median carina. Tegmina (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8D8D593CE41AE661504C5DD0773B3ED3" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">33</figureCitation>
) slender, longer than maximal width (2.59: 1), almost as wide at postnodal as prenodal area, veins ScP + 
<collectionCode id="D90EC98E9DCC603E02BE80535D91DDED" country="Chile" name="Departamento de Geologia, Universidad de Chile">R</collectionCode>
+ 
<collectionCode id="BF319B16D9E31F53A084AABE9878D955" country="0" name="Mohonk Preserve, Inc.">MP</collectionCode>
with several sensory pits, 
<collectionCode id="CD0BF1FC66D48677436516F921695BB4" country="0" name="Mohonk Preserve, Inc.">MP</collectionCode>
3 two branched; five postnodal closed cells with C1 smaller than C2, C5 placed next to C3, C4 distally displaced after the nodal line, im, r-m and anterior two-thirds of margin with white areas. Hind wing (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DFB56C3E49474A347BC26B1B0F973BF5" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">34</figureCitation>
) with lateral margin notched at CuA1, CuP, and A2, more strongly at A1; A2 not reaching posterior margin. Metatibiotarsal formula: (3+5)-6-5.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B03DF9E3AC02722ED30E83B10DE93158" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="male genitalia">
<paragraph id="1625AB1DF22CD4BB1EA5207503191419" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Male genitalia.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8A7742739AC902B303DF57585F63F622" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
Pygofer (Figs 
<figureCitation id="025616834D9354D00EDE9260C230D66C" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E2A11D242D316C7F775059684D91713E" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">36</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BB3B77B4EC1AEE070E426CBBCA6F8CFE" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9A704632F041D16B899557DF3AB96B8F" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">39</figureCitation>
) symmetrical, gradually narrowed towards the apex, with sinuate anterior and posterior margins. Pygopher with internal sulcus and slightly curved lateral margins in ventral view. Anal tube (Figs 
<figureCitation id="B308C4346613466FAFC9751D0F365B64" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="01F057F1FF666FACBD2C13C096B0DEAA" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38</figureCitation>
) in lateral view, hand-shaped, anal style slender, lateral lobes distally shorter than anal style, dorsolateral and middle parts each with a finger-like process, basolateral side with a finger-like process. Aedeagus (Figs 
<figureCitation id="9A9A48C43F5127A0B9A913FD64A8823A" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="437647FEA0269A195CB3D5055DCF4939" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">37</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="162DD3F394F6BB7A8B1DC2B6D0E18595" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="E96FC27664528EA770D629EA82B110C5" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">41</figureCitation>
) acuminate apically, with tubular periandrium, lateral lobes swelling on both sides, surface beset with scale-like productions, ventral lobe slender with acute apex, dorsal lobes with a short finger-like process; in ventral view, base wider. Gonostyli (Figs 
<figureCitation id="648BED4D1E48B99EB6C93B5ADC761B72" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">35</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="BF1D104A7BB820145B6C4E8E7BB035FF" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">36</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="598E660F49881A8F42BF875D3B31C70D" captionStart="Figures 31–41" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figures 31 - 41. Metanigrus gremius sp. nov., male 31 head and thorax, dorsal view 32 frons, ventral view 33 tegmina 34 wing 35, 38 pygofer, lateral view 36, 39 gonostyli and pygofer, ventral view 37 aedeagus, left lateral view 40 gonostyli, dorsal view 41 aedeagus, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.3 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1024.62226.figures31-41" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/520806" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">38-40</figureCitation>
) divided into two parts, inner process curved apically, tapering into a process; in lateral view, outer process convex and arcuate with nearly square process at apex; in ventral view, divergent, inner part beak-shaped backward, apex of outer process nearly fan-shaped.
</paragraph>
