<subSubSection id="EAEDFDD5E80E5BFDD4AE2532221E97DD" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B0B94532E388CB098D1235BAD2FAA984" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B9C21B5E9D0017D507643120F3CCA9F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
The species name is derived from the Latin adjective &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="73EA4566C44C8B088369D868DAC3FF14" authorityName="Lv &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Meenoplidae" genus="Metanigrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metanigrus gremius" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gremius">
<emphasis id="3EAFE81B9262413FBAA506E14C5D1FF5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Metanigrus gremius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot;, referring to general yellowish white.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D0BE1DEE0C46324DBE4B3F25E482D1D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="AB7216EA374A54C0F5BA051D4E398D66" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B3FACE34328EE2F33D6DD8D8C8575ED" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="1F73933E92F8EB2D247078FF4138FE4C" authorityName="Lv &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Meenoplidae" genus="Metanigrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metanigrus guttatus" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis id="19C5057246CC374B5D2AA5DEE9880788" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">Metanigrus guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from the latter in: (1) distal part of tegmina without large, black patch (distal part of tegmina with large, black patch in 
<taxonomicName id="248CB97A1027879BD56690871F389B3B" genus="M." lsidName="M. guttatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis id="A012C1B9DC6301672CE4C8B7EDEA9D93" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">M. guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) dorsolateral and middle parts of anal tube each with a finger-like process (only dorsolateral part of anal tube with a finger-like process in 
<taxonomicName id="8C55067FACCED8AF253DCC783D042A9B" genus="M." lsidName="M. guttatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis id="DE76F2806C9351233C7495291873F16A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">M. guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (3) outer process of gonostyli nearly square at apex in lateral view (outer process of gonostyli nearly fan-shaped at apex in lateral view in 
<taxonomicName id="570BB756D6668723E940D2884130775A" genus="M." lsidName="M. guttatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="197" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis id="68619AAD77DCC314094358CFD4DDA4A1" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="197">M. guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
